Gnathosoma
.

CHELICERA (
Fig. 1C
): movable digit 17 (17–18) long, without discernible teeth; fixed digit 19 (18–20) long, with three teeth and a tiny pilus dentilis near first tooth. PALP (
Fig. 12A
): trochanter devoid of setae; femur with a strong and spatulate seta and three simple setae; genu bearing a thick and four simple setae; tibial setae simple; division between tibia and tarsus undiscernible; tarsal apotele 2-tined. HYPOSTOME (
Fig. 13A
): weakly sclerotized, with only two pairs of hypostomal setae (
h1
and 
h2
) and deutosternal groove faint, without discernible denticles.

